message.content:
To calculate Return on Assets (ROA), use the formula:

\[
ROA = \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Average Total Assets}} \times 100\%
\]

Where:
- Net Profit = 146,127.58 (from income statement)
- Average Total Assets = \(\frac{\text{Beginning Assets} + \text{Ending Assets}}{2}\)

From the balance sheet:
- Beginning Total Assets (2023-12-31) = 16,000,000.00
- Ending Total Assets (2024-02-01) = 21,662,106.19

Calculate average total assets:
\[
\frac{16,000,000.00 + 21,662,106.19}{2} = \frac{37,662,106.19}{2} = 18,831,053.095
\]

Calculate ROA:
\[
ROA = \frac{146,127.58}{18,831,053.095} \times 100\% \approx 0.7757\%
\]

Rounded to two decimals: 0.78%
